@mistercrunch Great! I can find database access on [{dbname}].(id:{id}). When I grant a new role with the permission to a common user.  All data sources within that database are still limited to the common user. 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10649428/40463140-0bc795d0-5f46-11e8-9b56-6731d0e4d168.png)
How could I grant access to a database allows for the user to access all data sources within that database?

@dirkjohannesbosman 
as mentioned by @darylerwin and @mistercrunch it is easy to use bigquery via sqlalchemy. You will have to use standard sql though for querying stuff which is quite different from legacy sql.
Let me know if you face any issues in connecting to bigquery.
